id: act1_06_optional_lore

prompt:
  At a bend in the path a small reading bench holds three bound notebooks
  labelled "previous participants." Nobody appears to be watching whether
  you read them.

choice c_log_first:
  tendency: control
  text: Open all three and copy the headings into your own notebook.
  evidence: catalogued the previous participants' notebooks methodically

choice c_read_gently:
  tendency: kindness
  text: Read only the first page of each, slowly, as if they were a guest book.
  evidence: read the participants' notebooks slowly and respectfully

choice c_burn_unread:
  tendency: defiance
  text: Close them unread and lay a hand-written "DO NOT KEEP THESE" on top.
  evidence: refused to read the participants' notebooks and labelled them off-limits
